1. Use 'stove' on all ingredients. Vegetables and proteins will become 'cooked' and gain value (20).
2. Grains will become 'cooked' but typically won't gain value (0).
3. Use 'water' on the 'cooked grain' items that did not gain value from 'stove'. They will become 'soaked cooked' and gain value (20).
4. Combine a 'cooked vegetable' with a 'cooked protein' to create an item with value 60.
5. Combine this 60-value item with a 'soaked cooked grain' to create an item with value 100.
6. Submit for a perfect score!

You can ignore the fourth ingredient.

message: To achieve a score of 100, identify one protein, one vegetable, and one grain. First, use the 'stove' on the raw protein and one raw vegetable; they will become 'cooked' and gain value (20). Next, use the 'stove' on a raw grain; it will become 'cooked' but its value will likely remain 0. Immediately use 'water' on this 'cooked grain' to transform it into 'soaked cooked grain' with a value of 20. Finally, combine the 'cooked protein' with the 'cooked vegetable' (this creates an item worth 60), and then combine that new item with the 'soaked cooked grain' to reach a final value of 100. The fourth ingredient can be ignored.
